    "where ∆X = log X postlog X pre denotes log changes over time (after vs. before the arrival of AI chatbots).",
    "More generally, if baseline heterogeneity varies over time, the identifying assumption is that workers (firms) do not adopt (encourage) chatbots in response to anticipated shocks to their baseline human capital H i0 (or product demand Y j0).",
    "This assumption is consistent with the policy rules for adoption and encouragement (Equations (16) and (22)), which do not depend on baseline human capital or product demand.",
